      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 84: 🔴 Critical Issues - Accounts are deactivated whenever the last Activity stops, without checking whether there is an active call, pending call negotiation, file transfer, or other daemon work that still requires connectivity. Pressing Home during an active call or moving the app out of view can therefore deactivate the account and risk dropping the session. Gate this on an explicit app/daemon idle state before calling `setAccountsActive(false)`. Example:\\n```suggestion\\nif (--startedActivityCount \u003d\u003d 0\\n    \u0026\u0026 mPreferencesService.settings.enablePushNotifications\\n    \u0026\u0026 pushToken !\u003d null\\n    \u0026\u0026 !mCallService.hasCurrentCalls()\\n) {\\n    Log.d(TAG, \\\"App went to background with push enabled — deactivating accounts\\\")\\n    mAccountService.setAccountsActive(false)\\n}\\n```",
      "revId": "3446922e1706e8b99ca0b1ab4a13f7904afe4add",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
