      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 72: 🔴 Critical Issues - A high-priority FCM received while the app is already in background reactivates all accounts, but there is no matching deactivation after the push is handled when no Activity lifecycle transition occurs. This means the first background call/message push can leave daemon connections active indefinitely, largely defeating the battery-saving behavior introduced by this change. Reactivate only for the duration needed, or schedule/trigger deactivation again when processing completes and the app is still backgrounded. Example:\\n```suggestion\\nif (app?.mPreferencesService?.hasNetworkConnected() \u003d\u003d true) {\\n    app.mAccountService.setAccountsActive(true)\\n}\\n...\\nif (!isAppInForeground()\\n    \u0026\u0026 app?.mPreferencesService?.settings?.enablePushNotifications \u003d\u003d true\\n    \u0026\u0026 app.pushToken !\u003d null\\n) {\\n    app.mAccountService.setAccountsActive(false)\\n}\\n```\\nThe final condition should also account for active calls or other foreground services so an ongoing negotiation is not interrupted.",
