      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 585: 🟡 Suggestions - This now forces every account inactive, including accounts with no working push/proxy path. The caller currently checks only the application-level FCM token, not whether each account can actually receive proxy push notifications. If any account has `isDhtProxyEnabled \u003d\u003d false` or otherwise lacks push registration, it will become unreachable in background. Preserve active state for accounts that cannot be woken by push, or pass/account-check push capability before deactivation. Example:\\n```suggestion\\nval shouldDeactivate \u003d !active \u0026\u0026 a.isDhtProxyEnabled\\nJamiService.setAccountActive(a.accountId, if (shouldDeactivate) false else true)\\n```",
